an evening with david sedaris events at stanford an evening with david sedaris facebook twitter email print add to calendar the creative writing program at stanford university presents an evening with david sedaris with sardonic wit and incisive social critiques david sedaris has become one of america's pre eminent humor writers the great skill with which he slices through cultural euphemisms and political correctness proves that sedaris is a master of satire and one of the most observant writers addressing the human condition today david sedaris is the author of barrel fever and holidays on ice and the book of short stories squirrel seeks chipmunk as well as the collections of personal essays naked me talk pretty one day dress your family in corduroy and denim and when you are engulfed in flames there are over seven million copies of his books in print and they have been translated into 25 languages his work also appears on this american life and in the new yorker sedaris has been nominated for three grammy awards for best spoken word and best comedy album when sunday november 6 2011 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where memorial auditorium 551 serra mall map audience faculty staff students tags lecture reading humanities arts sponsor creative writing program contact 650 723 0011 krystalg stanford edu admission this is a ticketed event all tickets have been reserved but a limited number of tickets may be available at the door due to no shows ticket holders should arrive early as empty seats will be released at 6 50 pm permalink http events stanford edu events 291 29199 more info last modified november 1 2011
